Phone lines are a mess.
Gonna take Ma Bell a couple
of days to patch 'em up.

225
00:16:06.423 --> 00:16:08.883
- Especially around the holidays.
- Okay. thanks.

226
00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:12.303
- Heather! Did you count heads?
- Eleven. including me.

227
00:16:12.388 --> 00:16:17.225
Five boys. six girls.
four parents. two drivers and
a partridge in a pear tree.

228
00:16:25.109 --> 00:16:28.277
♪ Out of all the reindeer
you know you're the mastermind ♪

229
00:16:30.739 --> 00:16:35.034
♪ Run. run. Rudolph
Randolph ain't too far behind ♪

230
00:16:37.746 --> 00:16:41.124
♪ Run. run. Rudolph
Santa's gotta make it to town ♪

231
00:16:43.502 --> 00:16:47.255
♪ Santa. make him hurry
Tell him he can take the freeway down ♪♪

232
00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:51.926
This way!

233
00:16:52.011 --> 00:16:55.513
- Hold the plane!
[ Kate ] Did we miss the flight?

234
00:16:55.597 --> 00:16:58.182
No. you just made it.

235
00:16:58.267 --> 00:17:02.395
- Single seats in coach. Take whatever's free.
- Thank you.

236
00:17:02.479 --> 00:17:04.689
I get a window seat!

237
00:17:07.026 --> 00:17:09.110
[ Peter ]
You kids are in coach.
We're up here.

238
00:17:09.194 --> 00:17:11.946
Here are your seats.
Five "A" and "B"
and four "A" and "B."

239
00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:14.949
- I'll take your coats.
- Thank you.

240
00:17:15.034 --> 00:17:16.951
Fasten your seat belts.
please.

241
00:17:17.036 --> 00:17:19.620
- Champagne. please. It's free. isn't it?
- Oh. yes.

242
00:17:19.705 --> 00:17:23.374
We made it.
Do you believe it?

243
00:17:23.459 --> 00:17:25.626
Hope we didn't forget anything.

244
00:18:10.589 --> 00:18:13.007
What are you doing out of costume?

245
00:18:13.092 --> 00:18:15.009
Now get back and get dressed.

246
00:18:15.094 --> 00:18:17.220
I'm terribly sorry. I thought
you were our Santa Claus.

247
00:18:17.304 --> 00:18:19.222
[ Man ]
Your Santa Claus
is intoxicated.

248
00:18:19.306 --> 00:18:21.432
[ Woman ]
Oh. no.
Yes.

249
00:18:21.517 --> 00:18:24.602
It's disgraceful!
How can you allow a man—

250
00:18:24.686 --> 00:18:29.941
♪Jingle bells. jingle bells ♪

251
00:18:30.025 --> 00:18:32.777
[ Woman ]
What do you mean by drinking?
You know it's not allowed!

252
00:18:32.861 --> 00:18:36.531
[ Man #2 ] But it's cold.
A man's gotta do something
to keep warm.

253
00:18:36.615 --> 00:18:38.533
[ Man ]
I ought to take this cane and—

254
00:18:38.617 --> 00:18:43.246
[ Woman ]
Julia. get some black coffee
and plenty of it.

255
00:18:43.330 --> 00:18:45.289
[ Man #2 ]
Black with a little cream.

256
00:18:45.374 --> 00:18:47.583
Mom?

257
00:18:52.548 --> 00:18:55.341
Thank you.

258
00:18:55.425 --> 00:18:58.636
- That's real crystal. It's real.
- Yeah. So?

259
00:18:58.720 --> 00:19:02.974
- Put 'em in your purse. Put 'em!
- I can't do that.

260
00:19:03.058 --> 00:19:04.976
Put them in your purse!

261
00:19:05.060 --> 00:19:09.230
Uh. yeah. yeah.
fill it up. fill it up.
Fill it up. please.

262
00:19:09.314 --> 00:19:11.232
Thank you.

263
00:19:11.316 --> 00:19:14.735
Don't you feel like a heel
flying first class with
the kids back in coach?

264
00:19:14.820 --> 00:19:16.737
No. the kids are fine.

265
00:19:16.822 --> 00:19:20.992
Only flying I ever did as a kid
was in the family station wagon.
and it wasn't to France.

266
00:19:21.076 --> 00:19:24.412
We used to have to go over to
Aunt Laura and Uncle Arthur's house.

267
00:19:24.496 --> 00:19:27.373
The kids are okay. They're
having the time of their lives.

268
00:19:28.458 --> 00:19:30.459
Hello?

269
00:19:31.587 --> 00:19:33.588
Mom?

270
00:19:35.340 --> 00:19:37.341
Dad?

271
00:19:40.679 --> 00:19:43.472
Mom? Dad?

272
00:19:45.475 --> 00:19:48.227
Where are you guys?

273
00:19:48.312 --> 00:19:58.654
Buzz?

274
00:20:02.367 --> 00:20:04.285
Megan?

275
00:20:04.369 --> 00:20:08.956
Hello? Hello?

276
00:20:09.041 --> 00:20:12.043
Rod? Uncle Frank?

277
00:20:12.127 --> 00:20:14.462
Uncle Frank. is this a joke?

278
00:20:16.298 --> 00:20:19.300
Megan? Linnie?

279
00:20:21.845 --> 00:20:23.846
Is this a joke?

280
00:20:47.037 --> 00:20:51.540
It's only my imagination.
Only my imagination.

281
00:21:08.600 --> 00:21:12.186
The cars are still here.
They didn't go to the airport.

282
00:21:30.038 --> 00:21:33.874
I made my family disappear.

283
00:21:34.918 --> 00:21:37.128
Kevin. you're completely helpless.

284
00:21:37.212 --> 00:21:41.799
You know. Kevin. you're what
the French call les incompetents.

285
00:21:41.883 --> 00:21:45.136
Kevin. I'm going to feed you
to my tarantula.

286
00:21:45.220 --> 00:21:48.222
Kevin. you are such a disease.

287
00:21:48.307 --> 00:21:50.516
There are 15 people in this house...

288
00:21:50.600 --> 00:21:53.436
and you're the only one
who has to make trouble.

289
00:21:53.520 --> 00:21:56.897
Look what you did. you little jerk.

290
00:22:00.652 --> 00:22:03.821
I made my family disappear.

291
00:22:18.128 --> 00:22:22.214
I'm free! Free! Free!

292
00:22:32.100 --> 00:22:34.101
Wow!

293
00:22:40.067 --> 00:22:43.778
No clothes on anybody.
Sickening!

294
00:22:43.862 --> 00:22:48.032
Cool! Firecrackers!
I'll save these for later.

295
00:22:48.116 --> 00:22:51.118
Buzz. I'm going through
all your private stuff!

296
00:22:51.203 --> 00:22:54.163
You better come out and pound me!

297
00:22:57.459 --> 00:23:00.753
Buzz. your girlfriend!
Woof!

298
00:23:49.511 --> 00:23:51.512
Who is it?

299
00:23:54.975 --> 00:23:57.893
It's me. Snakes.
I got the stuff.

300
00:23:57.978 --> 00:24:01.105
Leave it on the doorstep
and get the hell out of here.

301
00:24:01.189 --> 00:24:04.400
[ Snakes ]
All right. Johnny.
But what about my money?

302
00:24:04.484 --> 00:24:08.028
[Johnny ] What money?
Acey said you had
some dough for me.

303
00:24:08.113 --> 00:24:11.115
Is that a fact?
How much do I owe you?

304
00:24:11.199 --> 00:24:14.076
Acey said 10%.

305
00:24:14.161 --> 00:24:16.871
Too bad Acey ain't
in charge no more.

306
00:24:16.955 --> 00:24:19.874
[ Snakes ] What do you mean?
- Guys. I'm eating junk and watching rubbish!

307
00:24:19.958 --> 00:24:22.960
You better come out and stop me!

308
00:24:23.044 --> 00:24:25.671
[Johnny ]
He'll call you
when he gets out.

309
00:24:25.755 --> 00:24:27.465
Hey.

310
00:24:27.549 --> 00:24:30.342
I tell you what I'm gonna
give you. Snakes.

311
00:24:31.928 --> 00:24:34.221
I'm gonna give you
to the count of 10...

312
00:24:34.306 --> 00:24:37.433
to get your ugly. yellow.

313
00:24:37.517 --> 00:24:39.643
no-good keister off my property...

314
00:24:39.728 --> 00:24:41.854
before I pump your guts full of lead.

315
00:24:41.938 --> 00:24:44.523
All right. Johnny.
I'm sorry. I'm goin'.

316
00:24:44.608 --> 00:24:47.193
One. two. ten!

317
00:25:02.417 --> 00:25:04.877
Keep the change. ya filthy animal.

318
00:25:06.505 --> 00:25:08.088
Mom!

319
00:25:19.434 --> 00:25:22.019
What's the matter?

320
00:25:22.103 --> 00:25:24.522
Honey?

321
00:25:24.606 --> 00:25:28.150
- I have a terrible feeling.
- About what?

322
00:25:29.236 --> 00:25:31.362
That we didn't do something.

323
00:25:31.446 --> 00:25:34.782
Oh. no. you feel that way
because we left in such a hurry.

324
00:25:34.866 --> 00:25:38.202
- We took care of evertyhing. Believe me.
- Did I turn off the coffee?

325
00:25:38.286 --> 00:25:41.205
No. I did.

326
00:25:41.289 --> 00:25:43.290
Did you lock up?

327
00:25:43.375 --> 00:25:45.292
Yeah.

328
00:25:45.377 --> 00:25:48.087
Did you close the garage?

329
00:25:50.090 --> 00:25:53.884
That's it. I forgot to close
the garage. That's it.

330
00:25:59.474 --> 00:26:01.809
No. that's not it.

331
00:26:02.978 --> 00:26:05.187
What else could we be forgetting?

332
00:26:09.067 --> 00:26:11.318
Kevin!

333
00:26:37.554 --> 00:26:40.222
Whoa!

334
00:26:41.224 --> 00:26:45.019
Whoa! Whoa!

335
00:26:53.737 --> 00:26:56.947
The captain's doing all he can.
Your phones are still out of order.

336
00:26:57.032 --> 00:27:01.452
We'll call as soon as we land. Kate.
I'm sure evertyhing's okay.

337
00:27:01.536 --> 00:27:05.205
It's horrible. Horrible.
Just horrible.

338
00:27:05.290 --> 00:27:08.375
How could we do this?
We forgot him.

339
00:27:08.460 --> 00:27:10.753
We didn't forget him.
We just... miscounted.

340
00:27:11.880 --> 00:27:14.131
What kind of mother am I?

341
00:27:14.215 --> 00:27:18.010
If it makes you feel any better.
I forgot my reading glasses.

342
00:27:22.641 --> 00:27:25.309
[ Policeman ]
Five families gone on one block alone.

343
00:27:25.393 --> 00:27:28.312
They all told me
from their own mouths.

344
00:27:28.396 --> 00:27:30.356
It's almost too easy.

345
00:27:30.440 --> 00:27:34.318
Check it out. All the houses
with nobody home...

346
00:27:34.402 --> 00:27:37.571
have automatic timers
on their lights.

347
00:27:37.656 --> 00:27:40.574
But I got it all figured out.
Watch this.

348
00:27:42.118 --> 00:27:45.537
Number 664 will be going on...

349
00:27:45.622 --> 00:27:48.916
right about... now.

350
00:27:50.585 --> 00:27:53.671
Wait. wait. wait.
wait. wait. wait.

351
00:27:53.755 --> 00:27:56.382
Number 672.

352
00:27:57.592 --> 00:28:00.302
right... now.

353
00:28:00.387 --> 00:28:03.597
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

354
00:28:03.682 --> 00:28:07.935
671 ... now.

355
00:28:10.063 --> 00:28:13.399
And that's the one. Marvin.
That's the silver tuna.

356
00:28:13.483 --> 00:28:15.651
Oh. it's very "G."

357
00:28:15.735 --> 00:28:18.696
Very "G." huh?
It's loaded.

358
00:28:18.780 --> 00:28:21.198
It's got lots of top flight goods.

359
00:28:21.282 --> 00:28:24.743
- Stereos. VCR's.
- Toys.

360
00:28:24.828 --> 00:28:29.331
Probably lookin' at
some very fine jewelry.
Possible cash hoard.

361
00:28:29.416 --> 00:28:33.669
Odd marketable securities.
Who knows?

362
00:28:33.753 --> 00:28:35.963
It's a gem.

363
00:28:36.047 --> 00:28:38.048
Grab your crowbar.

364
00:28:39.300 --> 00:28:41.301
Crowbars up.

365
00:28:43.179 --> 00:28:46.849
[ Man ]
♪ You're a rotter. Mr. Grinch ♪

366
00:28:47.976 --> 00:28:52.104
♪ You're the king of sinful sots ♪

367
00:28:52.188 --> 00:28:56.734
♪ Your heart's a dead tomato
splotched with moldy purple spots ♪

368
00:28:56.818 --> 00:29:00.446
♪ Mr. Grinch ♪

369
00:29:00.530 --> 00:29:03.782
You're a three-decker sauerkraut
and toadstool sandwich—

370
00:29:40.195 --> 00:29:44.323
- Which way?
- We'll go around back down
the basement. Follow me.

371
00:30:04.177 --> 00:30:06.261
I thought you said they were gone.

372
00:30:06.346 --> 00:30:10.182
- They were supposed to leave this morning.
- Let's get out of here.

373
00:30:46.719 --> 00:30:49.263
We have to use the phone. please.

374
00:30:49.347 --> 00:30:52.140
It's an emergency.
We really have to make a call.

375
00:30:52.225 --> 00:30:55.269
Please! Our brother's home alone.

376
00:30:55.353 --> 00:30:58.605
Give us the phone! Thank you.
I'm sorry. Thank you.

377
00:30:58.690 --> 00:31:01.692
Peter. I'm gonna call
the police. Why don't you
book us a flight home.

378
00:31:01.776 --> 00:31:06.446
Get some change out of here.
Call everybody you know.
Oh. Leslie.

379
00:31:06.531 --> 00:31:09.741
Here's my address book.
You and Frank call everybody
who lives on our street.

380
00:31:09.826 --> 00:31:11.743
Maybe somebody can help us.

381
00:31:11.828 --> 00:31:15.873
Hello? Hello? Hello?
She'll have to call you back.

382
00:31:21.045 --> 00:31:25.007
This is ridiculous. Only a wimp
would be hiding under a bed.

383
00:31:25.091 --> 00:31:29.219
And I can't be a wimp.
I'm the man of the house.

384
00:31:36.477 --> 00:31:39.396
Hey! I'm not afraid anymore!

385
00:31:40.815 --> 00:31:44.818
I said. I'm not afraid anymore!

386
00:31:44.903 --> 00:31:47.738
Do you hear me?
I'm not afraid anymore!

387
00:32:18.728 --> 00:32:20.729
Village Police Department.

388
00:32:20.813 --> 00:32:24.358
Hi. Look. I'm calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone.

389
00:32:24.442 --> 00:32:27.861
Our phones are out of order.
so I'd like somebody
to go to our house...

390
00:32:27.946 --> 00:32:29.863
and tell him we're
coming home to get him.

391
00:32:29.948 --> 00:32:32.032
Let me connect you
with Family Crisis Intervention.

392
00:32:32.116 --> 00:32:34.993
- It's not a family crisis.
- Hold on.

393
00:32:36.871 --> 00:32:40.374
Larry. can you pick up?
There's some lady on hold.
sounds kind of hyper.

394
00:32:40.458 --> 00:32:43.210
- What line. Rose?
- Uh. two.

395
00:32:43.294 --> 00:32:45.921
Family Crisis Intervention.
Sergeant Balzak.

396
00:32:46.005 --> 00:32:49.007
I am calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone.

397
00:32:49.092 --> 00:32:51.009
Has the child been involved
in a violent altercation...

398
00:32:51.094 --> 00:32:53.929
with a drunken and/or mentally
ill member of his immediate family?

399
00:32:54.013 --> 00:32:57.975
- No.
- Has he been involved
in a household accident?

400
00:32:58.059 --> 00:33:00.310
I don't know. I don't—
I hope not.

401
00:33:00.395 --> 00:33:02.896
Has the child ingested any poison...

402
00:33:02.981 --> 00:33:05.691
and/or any other object that has
become lodged in his throat?

403
00:33:05.775 --> 00:33:09.403
No. he's just home alone!
I would like somebody
to go over to the house...

404
00:33:09.487 --> 00:33:12.322
and see that he's all right.
just to check on him.

405
00:33:12.407 --> 00:33:16.076
You want us to go to your house
just to check on him?

406
00:33:16.160 --> 00:33:19.621
- Yes!
- Let me connect you
with the police department.

407
00:33:19.706 --> 00:33:22.207
- They just transferred me to you.
- Rose?

408
00:33:22.291 --> 00:33:24.751
- Yeah?
- Hyper on two. Hold on. please.

409
00:33:24.836 --> 00:33:28.797
- No. please don't hang up. Please. don't—
- Any luck?

410
00:33:28.881 --> 00:33:32.509
No. We couldn't get anybody.

411
00:33:32.593 --> 00:33:36.430
[ Kate ] Leslie?
I'm sorry. Kate. Nothing but
a bunch of answering machines.

412
00:33:38.641 --> 00:33:42.310
Somebody pick up.
Pick up!

413
00:33:42.395 --> 00:33:44.938
- Hi. ma'am. It's you again.
- Yeah. hi. Look.

414
00:33:45.023 --> 00:33:47.899
I'm calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone. and I—

415
00:33:47.984 --> 00:33:51.987
Okay. okay. We'll send a policeman
over to your house to check on your son.

416
00:34:22.185 --> 00:34:24.895
There's no one home.
The house looks secure.

417
00:34:24.979 --> 00:34:28.065
Tell 'em to count their kids again.
[ Man ] Ten-four.

418
00:34:28.149 --> 00:34:30.734
I can't believe you can't
bump somebody or ask somebody—

419
00:34:30.818 --> 00:34:33.528
I'm sorry. but there's
no way I can do that.

420
00:34:33.613 --> 00:34:35.530
Isn't there a way if you ask somebody?

421
00:34:35.615 --> 00:34:38.158
- If you explained this is an emergency.
- I wish I could—

422
00:34:38.242 --> 00:34:40.744
They're sending a policeman over
to the house to check on Kevin.

423
00:34:40.828 --> 00:34:45.165
- That's a relief. Everything here is booked.
- There's nothing to Chicago?

424
00:34:45.249 --> 00:34:48.585
There's nothing to Chicago.
New York. Nashville.
You name it. Evertyhing's gone.

425
00:34:48.669 --> 00:34:53.090
- What about a private plane?
- No. I'm sorry.
We don't do that.

426
00:34:53.174 --> 00:34:56.218
The only thing they have
is a booking for all of us
on Friday morning.

427
00:34:56.302 --> 00:34:58.553
Friday morning?
That's two days away.

428
00:34:58.638 --> 00:35:01.098
Look. honey. the kids are exhausted.
You are exhausted.

429
00:35:01.182 --> 00:35:03.850
There's absolutely nothing
more we can do in this airport.

430
00:35:03.935 --> 00:35:08.063
I say we go to Rob's.
call the police again.
and they can get back to us.

431
00:35:08.147 --> 00:35:11.942
Kevin is home all by himself.
I'm not leaving here
unless it's on an airplane.

432
00:35:12.026 --> 00:35:13.944
Madame. we are doing
evertyhing we can.

433
00:35:14.028 --> 00:35:17.989
If you want to stay
at the airport. maybe
we can get you on standby.

434
00:35:18.074 --> 00:35:21.535
It is a possibility
that a seat will open up.

435
00:35:21.619 --> 00:35:24.746
- Is that okay?
- Yes. I'll wait.

436
00:35:24.831 --> 00:35:27.749
[ Man ]
♪ Bells will be ringing ♪

437
00:35:27.834 --> 00:35:29.751
♪ The glad. glad news ♪

438
00:35:29.836 --> 00:35:33.463
- Bye. I'll miss you.
- Bye.

439
00:35:33.548 --> 00:35:35.841
Find Kevin.
♪ Oh. what a Christmas ♪

440
00:35:35.925 --> 00:35:38.593
♪ To have the blues ♪
Don't you get lost.

441
00:35:38.678 --> 00:35:40.804
Good-bye.

442
00:35:40.888 --> 00:35:42.806
[ Frank ]
Good-bye. Kate.

443
00:35:42.890 --> 00:35:45.976
♪ Please come home for Christmas ♪

444
00:35:47.353 --> 00:35:51.481
♪ 'Cause I'll be happy at Christmas ♪

445
00:35:51.566 --> 00:35:53.567
♪ Once again ♪♪

446
00:35:56.737 --> 00:36:00.198
I took a shower.
washing every body part
with actual soap.

447
00:36:00.283 --> 00:36:04.828
including all my major crevices.
including in between my toes
and in my belly button.

448
00:36:04.912 --> 00:36:07.372
which I never did before.
but sort of enjoyed.

449
00:36:07.456 --> 00:36:10.125
I washed my hair
with adult-formula shampoo...

450
00:36:10.209 --> 00:36:13.378
and used cream rinse
for thatjust-washed shine.

451
00:36:13.462 --> 00:36:17.507
I can't seem to find
my toothbrush. so I'll pick one
up when I go out today.

452
00:36:17.592 --> 00:36:19.634
Other than that. I'm in good shape.

453
00:36:53.961 --> 00:36:55.921
Whoa!

454
00:37:09.810 --> 00:37:13.104
All right!
Buzz's life savings.

455
00:37:40.174 --> 00:37:43.093
I thought the Murphys
went to Florida.

456
00:37:58.985 --> 00:38:02.529
You know. you're one
of the great cat burglars
of the world. Marv.

457
00:38:02.613 --> 00:38:05.198
You think you could keep it
down a little in there?

458
00:38:05.283 --> 00:38:10.120
Hi. you've reached the Murphys.
Please leave a message
after you hear the beep.

459
00:38:10.204 --> 00:38:15.000
Chuck. this is Peter McCallister
again. and we're still in Paris
at my brother's apartment.

460
00:38:15.084 --> 00:38:18.211
Let me give you
the number here. okay?
The country code is 3-3.

461
00:38:18.296 --> 00:38:20.213
The area code is 1-4.

462
00:38:20.298 --> 00:38:24.551
- And the number is 694-8764.
- Hey. Harry?

463
00:38:24.635 --> 00:38:28.638
- Yeah?
