533
00:45:49.580 --> 00:45:52.540
[ Harry ]
We'll come back tomorrow.
Maybe they'll be gone by then.

534
00:45:52.624 --> 00:45:56.711
We'd better get out of here
before somebody sees us.

535
00:45:56.795 --> 00:46:01.799
♪ In the new old-fashioned way ♪♪

536
00:46:25.407 --> 00:46:27.617
Attention! Attention!

537
00:46:27.701 --> 00:46:31.621
- Look what I have found in "ze" kitchen!
- Frank. those are for later.

538
00:46:31.705 --> 00:46:33.706
Frank?

539
00:46:35.083 --> 00:46:38.961
Mes petites enfants.
do you want a little shrimp. eh?

540
00:46:39.046 --> 00:46:42.298
Oper-
Do you speak English?

541
00:46:42.382 --> 00:46:45.218
Parlez anglais?

542
00:46:45.302 --> 00:46:47.303
Is there— I mean—

543
00:46:47.387 --> 00:46:52.308
Est ce qui un person qui parle anglais?

544
00:46:52.392 --> 00:46:55.478
Did you get anybody? I'm looking for my son!
Do you know where he is?

545
00:46:55.562 --> 00:47:00.900
I can't find anybody.
They've all gone shopping.
Nobody's home for the holidays.

546
00:47:00.984 --> 00:47:03.110
[ Peter ]
Never mind. Forget it.

547
00:47:03.195 --> 00:47:05.238
This is so pointless.

548
00:47:05.322 --> 00:47:09.075
- What?
- We're here rotting in this apartment.

549
00:47:09.159 --> 00:47:11.369
Kevin's at home.
Mom's at the airport.

550
00:47:11.453 --> 00:47:13.788
- So?
- You're not at all
worried about Kevin?

551
00:47:13.872 --> 00:47:15.790
Why should I be?

552
00:47:15.874 --> 00:47:19.418
He's acted like a jerk too many times.
and this time he caught it in the butt.

553
00:47:19.503 --> 00:47:24.048
But he's so little and helpless.
Don't you think he's flipped out?

554
00:47:24.132 --> 00:47:27.343
The little trout can use
a couple of days in the real world.

555
00:47:27.427 --> 00:47:29.804
You're not worried that something
might happen to him?

556
00:47:29.888 --> 00:47:32.348
No. For three reasons.

557
00:47:32.432 --> 00:47:35.101
"A": I'm not that lucky.

558
00:47:35.185 --> 00:47:37.520
Two: We have smoke detectors.

559
00:47:37.604 --> 00:47:41.566
And "D": We live in the most
boring street in the United
States ofAmerica...

560
00:47:41.650 --> 00:47:46.070
where nothing even remotely dangerous
will ever happen. period.

561
00:48:13.181 --> 00:48:16.601
[Johnny's Voice ] Who is it?
- It's Little Nero's. sir. I have your pizza.

562
00:48:16.685 --> 00:48:19.896
Leave it on the doorstep
and get the hell outta here.

563
00:48:19.980 --> 00:48:22.773
Okay.

564
00:48:22.858 --> 00:48:25.109
Um. well. what about the money?

565
00:48:26.236 --> 00:48:27.904
What money?

566
00:48:27.988 --> 00:48:31.407
Well. you have to pay
for your pizza. sir.

567
00:48:31.491 --> 00:48:33.743
[Johnny ]
Is that a fact?

568
00:48:33.827 --> 00:48:36.037
How much do I owe you?

569
00:48:36.121 --> 00:48:39.457
Uh. that'll be
$11.80. sir.

570
00:48:45.756 --> 00:48:49.175
Keep the change.
ya filthy animal.

571
00:48:51.011 --> 00:48:52.929
- Cheapskate.
- Hey.

572
00:48:53.013 --> 00:48:56.807
I'm gonna give you to the count
of 10 to get your ugly.

573
00:48:56.892 --> 00:49:00.227
yellow. no-good keister
off my property...

574
00:49:00.312 --> 00:49:02.521
before I pump your guts
full of lead.

575
00:49:02.606 --> 00:49:04.523
One. two. ten!

576
00:49:33.512 --> 00:49:36.514
A lovely cheese pizza just for me.

577
00:49:39.977 --> 00:49:42.186
[ Woman Over P.A ]
To Dallas-Fort Worth.

578
00:49:45.565 --> 00:49:47.984
We have the $500.
the pocket translator.

579
00:49:48.068 --> 00:49:50.778
the two first-class seats—
that's an upgrade from your coach—

580
00:49:50.862 --> 00:49:54.657
- Is that a real Rolex?
- Do you think it is?

581
00:49:54.741 --> 00:49:57.451
- No.
- But who can tell?

582
00:49:57.536 --> 00:50:01.497
- I also have a ring.
- That is beautiful!

583
00:50:01.581 --> 00:50:04.125
Come on. They're boarding.

584
00:50:04.209 --> 00:50:07.712
This gal has offered us
two first-class tickets
if we go Friday.

585
00:50:07.796 --> 00:50:11.340
Plus a ring. a watch.
a pocket translator. $500 and—

586
00:50:11.425 --> 00:50:14.176
- The earrings. You love the earrings.
- She's got her own earrings.

587
00:50:14.261 --> 00:50:16.929
A whole shoe box full
of 'em. Dangley ones.

588
00:50:17.014 --> 00:50:19.015
- Come on. come on.
- No. but—

589
00:50:19.099 --> 00:50:21.142
I'm desperate.

590
00:50:21.226 --> 00:50:23.102
I'm begging you.

591
00:50:23.186 --> 00:50:26.647
From a mother to a mother. please.

592
00:50:28.108 --> 00:50:30.735
- Oh. Ed.
- Please.

593
00:50:30.819 --> 00:50:33.571
[ Ed ]
Oh. all right.

594
00:50:39.161 --> 00:50:41.203
"Dear Santa Claus.
I got a little sister last year.

595
00:50:41.288 --> 00:50:43.497
This year I'd rather
have some clay dough."

596
00:50:57.596 --> 00:50:59.513
I didn't mean it.

597
00:50:59.598 --> 00:51:02.767
If you come back. I'll never
be a pain in the butt again.

598
00:51:02.851 --> 00:51:05.853
I promise. Good night.

599
00:51:25.040 --> 00:51:29.043
[ Man ]
♪ I'm dreaming ♪

600
00:51:29.127 --> 00:51:33.506
♪ Of a white Christmas ♪

601
00:51:33.590 --> 00:51:38.010
♪Just like the ones I used to know ♪

602
00:51:40.097 --> 00:51:44.767
♪ Where those treetops glisten ♪

603
00:51:44.851 --> 00:51:47.853
♪ And children listen ♪

604
00:51:47.938 --> 00:51:50.106
♪ To hear ♪

605
00:51:50.190 --> 00:51:53.442
♪ Sleigh bells in the snow ♪

606
00:51:53.527 --> 00:51:56.237
♪ The snow ♪

607
00:52:04.037 --> 00:52:09.333
♪ With every Christmas card I write ♪

608
00:52:10.752 --> 00:52:14.463
♪ May your days. may your days
