609
00:52:14.548 --> 00:52:19.093
♪ And bright ♪♪

610
00:52:47.038 --> 00:52:49.456
Are those microwave dinners any good?

611
00:52:49.541 --> 00:52:52.918
- I don't know.
- I'll give 'em a whirl.

612
00:52:57.757 --> 00:52:59.925
For the kids.

613
00:53:02.262 --> 00:53:04.847
Hold on.
I got a coupon for that.

614
00:53:04.931 --> 00:53:07.641
It was in the paper this morning.

615
00:53:11.188 --> 00:53:14.106
- $19.83.
- Okay.

616
00:53:17.569 --> 00:53:19.737
Are you here all by yourself?

617
00:53:21.198 --> 00:53:25.326
Ma'am. I'm eight years old.
You think I would be here alone?

618
00:53:25.410 --> 00:53:27.745
I don't think so.

619
00:53:27.829 --> 00:53:30.122
- Where's your mom?
- My mom's in the car.

620
00:53:30.207 --> 00:53:32.625
- And where is your father?
- He's at work.

621
00:53:32.709 --> 00:53:35.502
- What about your brothers
and your sisters?
- I'm an only child.

622
00:53:35.587 --> 00:53:38.088
- Where do you live?
- I can't tell you that.

623
00:53:38.173 --> 00:53:41.258
- Why not?
- 'Cause you're a stranger.

624
00:54:19.297 --> 00:54:23.092
Hello. Kevin!

625
00:54:24.344 --> 00:54:27.805
Shut up.

626
00:54:40.735 --> 00:54:42.653
[ Harry ]
I don't get it.

627
00:54:42.737 --> 00:54:45.447
I mean. right now it looks
like there's nobody home.

628
00:54:45.532 --> 00:54:49.118
Last night the place is jumpin'.

629
00:54:49.202 --> 00:54:52.997
Somethin' ain't right.
Go check it out.

630
00:55:01.548 --> 00:55:03.465
Now?

631
00:55:03.550 --> 00:55:05.467
No. tomorrow. egghead. Now!

632
00:55:05.552 --> 00:55:08.220
Go ahead!

633
00:55:08.305 --> 00:55:10.556
"Now?"

634
00:55:27.824 --> 00:55:30.242
Shit.

635
00:55:32.037 --> 00:55:34.955
Get the hell outta here.
All right. Johnny.

636
00:55:35.040 --> 00:55:38.167
- But what about my money?
[Johnny ] What money?

637
00:55:38.251 --> 00:55:41.003
Acey said you had some dough for me.

638
00:55:41.087 --> 00:55:45.966
[Johnny ] Is that a fact?
How much do I owe you?
- Acey said 10%.

639
00:55:46.051 --> 00:55:51.055
Two bad Acey ain't in charge no more.
What do you mean?

640
00:55:51.139 --> 00:55:54.558
[Johnny ] He's upstairs taking a bath.

641
00:55:54.642 --> 00:55:57.353
He'll call you when he gets out.

642
00:55:57.437 --> 00:55:59.355
Hey.

643
00:55:59.439 --> 00:56:02.483
I tell you what
I'm gonna give you. Snakes.

644
00:56:02.567 --> 00:56:06.403
Snakes?
I'm gonna give you
to the count of 10...

645
00:56:06.488 --> 00:56:08.822
to get your ugly. yellow.

646
00:56:08.907 --> 00:56:13.369
no-good keister off my property
before I pump your guts full of lead.

647
00:56:13.453 --> 00:56:16.163
All right. Johnny. I'm sorry.
I'm goin'.

648
00:56:16.247 --> 00:56:19.208
One. two. ten!

649
00:56:38.436 --> 00:56:41.605
Keep the change. ya filthy animal.

650
00:56:45.610 --> 00:56:49.988
- What happened?
- I don't know who's in there. but
somebody just got blown away!

651
00:56:50.073 --> 00:56:52.574
- Huh?
- Somebody beat us to the job.
They're in there!

652
00:56:52.659 --> 00:56:56.703
Two of 'em. There was arguing.
One of 'em blew the other one away.

653
00:56:56.788 --> 00:56:58.497
- Who?
- I don't know.

654
00:56:58.581 --> 00:57:01.041
I thought I recognized
one of their voices.

655
00:57:01.126 --> 00:57:04.336
And I know I heard that name Snakes before.

656
00:57:04.421 --> 00:57:06.922
Snakes? Snakes. Snakes.

657
00:57:07.006 --> 00:57:09.133
- I don't know no Snakes.
- Snakes.

658
00:57:09.217 --> 00:57:11.844
Let's get out of here.

659
00:57:14.180 --> 00:57:16.890
Hold it. hold it.
Let's wait and see who it is.

660
00:57:16.975 --> 00:57:18.892
We work this neighborhood too.

661
00:57:18.977 --> 00:57:21.770
- Yeah.
Supposin' the cops finger us for a job...

662
00:57:21.855 --> 00:57:24.898
and they start asking us questions
about a murder in the area.

663
00:57:24.983 --> 00:57:28.152
Wouldn't it be nice
to have a face to go
with their questions?

664
00:57:29.988 --> 00:57:31.947
That's a good idea.

665
00:57:32.031 --> 00:57:35.492
Of course it's a good idea.
Snakes?

666
00:57:35.577 --> 00:57:38.495
He sounded like a snake.

667
00:57:42.542 --> 00:57:45.669
Everything's full.

668
00:57:45.753 --> 00:57:47.671
Evertyhing's full?

669
00:57:47.755 --> 00:57:50.007
I'm very sorry.
but it is Christmas Eve.

670
00:57:50.091 --> 00:57:52.259
What about another airline?

671
00:57:57.682 --> 00:58:00.642
Nothing available. May I help you get
a hotel room in the city?

672
00:58:00.727 --> 00:58:04.271
Tomorrow afternoon we can
get you a flight to Chicago.
I can't wait that long.

673
00:58:04.355 --> 00:58:08.775
I'm terribly sorry. ma'am.
but we're doing absolutely
everything we can.

674
00:58:12.906 --> 00:58:16.074
Go ahead. I'm in your way.
You have places to go. people to see.

675
00:58:16.159 --> 00:58:19.495
You got a ticket there.
That's good. Excuse me. Look.

676
00:58:19.579 --> 00:58:23.624
I have been awake for almost 60 hours.
I'm tired and I'm dirty.

677
00:58:23.708 --> 00:58:28.170
I have been from Chicago
to Paris to Dallas to-
Where the hell am I?

678
00:58:28.254 --> 00:58:30.297
Scranton.

679
00:58:30.381 --> 00:58:33.050
I am trying to get home
to my eight-year-old son!

680
00:58:33.134 --> 00:58:36.553
And now that I'm this close.
you're telling me it's hopeless?

681
00:58:36.638 --> 00:58:40.307
- I'm sorry.
- No. No. no. no. No Way. This is Christmas!

682
00:58:40.391 --> 00:58:42.309
The season of perpetual hope!

683
00:58:42.393 --> 00:58:46.188
- Ma'am. if I—
- If I have to get out
on your runway and hitchhike.

684
00:58:46.272 --> 00:58:48.232
if it costs me everything I own.

685
00:58:48.316 --> 00:58:51.193
if I have to sell my soul
to the devil himself.

686
00:58:51.277 --> 00:58:54.488
I am going to get home to my son.

687
00:58:54.572 --> 00:58:58.700
- Ma'am. if there was anything at
all I could do for you today-
- Do it.

688
00:58:58.785 --> 00:59:01.411
- Do anything.
- I can get you a hotel room.

689
00:59:01.496 --> 00:59:03.956
- What?
- Excuse me.

690
00:59:04.040 --> 00:59:09.753
Can you excuse us for a second?
Can I see you for a second?
Please. Excuse us. Come.

691
00:59:09.837 --> 00:59:13.048
Couldn't help but hearin'
you got a little bit of a dilemma there.

692
00:59:13.132 --> 00:59:15.759
We got a crisis ourselves.

693
00:59:15.843 --> 00:59:19.346
Allow me to introduce myself.
Gus Polinski. How are you?

694
00:59:19.430 --> 00:59:22.849
Polka king of the Midwest?

695
00:59:25.728 --> 00:59:28.480
The Kenosha Kickers?

696
00:59:28.565 --> 00:59:30.232
- Hi there.
- Hiya.

697
00:59:30.316 --> 00:59:33.193
No? That's okay. I thought
you might've recognized—

698
00:59:33.278 --> 00:59:36.238
Antways. uh. I had
a few hits a few years ago.

699
00:59:36.322 --> 00:59:39.616
Uh. that's why. you know—
"Polka. Polka. Polka"?

700
00:59:39.701 --> 00:59:42.077
♪ Polka. polka. polka ♪

701
00:59:42.161 --> 00:59:44.204
No? "Twin Lakes Polka."

702
00:59:44.289 --> 00:59:47.749
"Yamahoozie Polka."
a.k.a. "Kiss Me Polka."

703
00:59:47.834 --> 00:59:50.502
- "Polka Twist."
- These are songs?

704
00:59:50.587 --> 00:59:54.006
Yeah. Yeah. We-
Some fairly big hits for us.

705
00:59:54.090 --> 00:59:56.717
- You know. in the early '70s. you know?
- Oh.

706
00:59:56.801 --> 00:59:59.428
Yeah. we sold
about 623 copies of that.

707
00:59:59.512 --> 01:00:02.180
- In Chicago?
- No. Sheboygan. Very big in Sheboygan.

708
01:00:02.265 --> 01:00:04.433
I'm sorry. Did you say
you could help me?

709
01:00:04.517 --> 01:00:06.685
Anyway. I'm rambling on here.

710
01:00:06.769 --> 01:00:09.855
Our flight was canceled.
so we gotta drive.

711
01:00:09.939 --> 01:00:13.525
So. uh. see the guy
in the yellowjacket over there
by the Budget sign?

712
01:00:13.610 --> 01:00:17.362
He's gonna rent us
a nice big. uh. van. and we're
gonna drive to Milwaukee.

713
01:00:17.447 --> 01:00:21.783
I heard you had some problems
here. uh. gettin' to Chicago
to see your kid or somethin'?

714
01:00:21.868 --> 01:00:25.954
Uh. my son. He-
We left and he's there.

715
01:00:26.039 --> 01:00:30.167
Aw. geez.
If you have to get to Chicago.
we'll gladly drive you.

716
01:00:30.251 --> 01:00:32.544
It's on the way to Milwaukee.

717
01:00:32.629 --> 01:00:35.297
- You'd give me a ride?
- Sure we will. Why not. you know?

718
01:00:35.381 --> 01:00:37.924
- You gotta get home and see your kid.
- A ride to Chicago?

719
01:00:38.009 --> 01:00:39.885
Sure. You know.
it's Christmastime.

720
01:00:39.969 --> 01:00:42.512
Thank you.
Oh. thank you.

721
01:00:42.597 --> 01:00:44.931
If you don't mind goin'
with some polka bums.

722
01:00:45.016 --> 01:00:46.933
No. I'd love to.

723
01:01:08.623 --> 01:01:11.541
- Hey. Marv. Marv. Marv.
- What?

724
01:01:11.626 --> 01:01:14.127
Look at this.

725
01:01:18.675 --> 01:01:23.053
I think we're gettin' scammed
by a "kindygartener."

726
01:01:53.126 --> 01:01:55.752
Dad. can you come here and help me?

727
01:02:00.216 --> 01:02:04.469
Remember that kid we saw the other day?
He lives here.

728
01:02:04.554 --> 01:02:07.472
Well. if the kid's there.
the parents gotta be.

729
01:02:07.557 --> 01:02:10.142
He's home alone.

730
01:02:17.984 --> 01:02:20.360
You gotta be kiddin'.
You wanna come back tonight?

731
01:02:20.445 --> 01:02:22.362
- Uh-huh.
- Even with the kid here?

732
01:02:22.447 --> 01:02:24.573
- Uh-huh.
- I don't think that's a good idea.

733
01:02:24.657 --> 01:02:28.160
That house is the only
reason we started workin'
this block in the first place.

734
01:02:28.244 --> 01:02:30.954
Ever since I laid eyes
on that house. I wanted it.

735
01:02:31.038 --> 01:02:33.415
So let's take it
one step at a time. okay?

736
01:02:33.499 --> 01:02:37.043
We'll unload the van.
We'll get a bite to eat.
We'll come back about 9:00.

737
01:02:37.128 --> 01:02:40.046
- 9:00.
- This way it's dark then.

738
01:02:40.131 --> 01:02:43.258
Yeah. Kids are scared of the dark.

739
01:02:43.342 --> 01:02:46.219
You're afraid of the dark too.
Marv. You know you are.

740
01:02:46.304 --> 01:02:49.014
No. I'm not!

741
01:02:49.098 --> 01:02:51.600
- Yes. you are.
- I'm not. not. not.

742
01:02:51.684 --> 01:02:55.937
- You are so.
- Mom. where are you?

743
01:03:09.327 --> 01:03:11.244
Do you play?

744
01:03:11.329 --> 01:03:13.413
You want to try it?
Go ahead. Try it.

745
01:03:13.498 --> 01:03:15.791
- Try it. Try it.
- No.

746
01:03:15.875 --> 01:03:17.918
Okay.

747
01:03:42.109 --> 01:03:45.612
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

748
01:03:45.696 --> 01:03:49.658
- Hey. nice shoes.
- Oh. thanks.

749
01:03:49.742 --> 01:03:53.411
Is he still here?
It's really important
that I see him.

750
01:03:53.496 --> 01:03:58.792
He's getting in his car.
I guess if you hurry.
you can catch him.

751
01:03:58.876 --> 01:04:03.338
Damn! How low can you get?
Givin' Kris Kringle a parking
ticket on Christmas Eve.

752
01:04:03.422 --> 01:04:06.550
What's next? Rabies shots
for the Easter Bunny?

753
01:04:06.634 --> 01:04:09.261
Santa. hold on!

754
01:04:09.345 --> 01:04:11.471
Can I talk to you for a minute?

755
01:04:11.556 --> 01:04:14.558
If you make it quick.
Santa's got a little
get-together he's late for.

756
01:04:14.642 --> 01:04:16.560
Okay. I know you're not
the real Santa Claus.

757
01:04:16.644 --> 01:04:20.564
What makes you say that?
Just out of curiosity.

758
01:04:20.648 --> 01:04:23.316
I'm old enough to know how it works.

759
01:04:23.401 --> 01:04:26.486
- All right.
- But I also know that you work for him.

760
01:04:26.571 --> 01:04:29.614
- And I'd like you to give him a message.
- Shoot.

761
01:04:29.699 --> 01:04:33.827
I'm Kevin McCallister.
671 Lincoln Boulevard.

762
01:04:33.911 --> 01:04:36.580
- Do you need the phone number?
- No. that's all right.

763
01:04:36.664 --> 01:04:38.874
Okay. This is extremely important.

764
01:04:38.958 --> 01:04:43.795
Would you please tell him that.
instead of presents this year.
I just want my family back.

765
01:04:43.880 --> 01:04:48.800
No toys. Nothing
but Peter. Kate. Buzz.
Megan. Linnie and Jeff.

766
01:04:48.885 --> 01:04:51.094
And my aunt and my cousins.

767
01:04:51.178 --> 01:04:54.431
And. if he has time.
my Uncle Frank. Okay?

768
01:04:56.100 --> 01:04:59.269
Okay. I'll see what I can do.

769
01:04:59.353 --> 01:05:02.314
- Thanks.
- Wait. Hold on a second.

770
01:05:02.398 --> 01:05:05.567
My elf took the last of the
candy canes home to her boyfriend.

771
01:05:05.651 --> 01:05:07.694
- That's okay.
- No. no. no. Don't be silly.

772
01:05:07.778 --> 01:05:10.780
Everybody who sees Santa
has gotta get... somethin'.

773
01:05:10.865 --> 01:05:13.074
Here. Hold out
your little paw there.

774
01:05:13.159 --> 01:05:16.286
There you go.
Don't spoil your dinner.

775
01:05:16.370 --> 01:05:18.997
I won't. Thanks.

776
01:05:29.884 --> 01:05:32.510
Son of a—

