01:08:12.505 --> 01:08:15.757
♪ Born to be our friend ♪

808
01:08:15.841 --> 01:08:21.346
♪ Fall on your knees ♪

809
01:08:21.430 --> 01:08:24.891
♪ Oh. hear ♪

810
01:08:24.975 --> 01:08:28.561
♪ The angel voices ♪

811
01:08:28.646 --> 01:08:30.897
- Merry Christmas.
♪ O night ♪

812
01:08:30.981 --> 01:08:32.440
Huh?

813
01:08:32.525 --> 01:08:34.609
♪ Divine ♪
- May I sit down?

814
01:08:34.693 --> 01:08:37.237
♪ O night ♪

815
01:08:37.321 --> 01:08:41.282
♪ When Christ was born ♪

816
01:08:41.367 --> 01:08:44.953
♪ O night ♪

817
01:08:45.037 --> 01:08:49.582
That's my granddaughter up there.
The little red-haired girl.

818
01:08:49.667 --> 01:08:53.461
- ♪ O holy night ♪
- She's about your age.

819
01:08:53.546 --> 01:08:55.797
- Do you know her?
- No.

820
01:08:55.881 --> 01:08:58.967
- You live next to me. don't you?
- Yeah.

821
01:08:59.051 --> 01:09:03.555
You can say hello when you see me.
You don't have to be afraid.

822
01:09:03.639 --> 01:09:07.559
There's a lot of things
going around about me.
but none of it's true.

823
01:09:07.643 --> 01:09:09.561
Okay?

824
01:09:09.645 --> 01:09:11.855
- You been a good boy this year?
- I think so.

825
01:09:11.939 --> 01:09:14.065
Swear to it?

826
01:09:14.150 --> 01:09:16.860
- No.
- Yeah. I had a feeling.

827
01:09:16.944 --> 01:09:20.113
Well. this is the place to be
if you're feeling bad about yourself.

828
01:09:20.197 --> 01:09:23.116
- It is?
- I think so.

829
01:09:23.200 --> 01:09:25.910
- Are you feeling bad about yourself?
- No.

830
01:09:29.999 --> 01:09:32.417
I've been kind of a pain lately.

831
01:09:32.501 --> 01:09:34.919
I said some things I shouldn't have.

832
01:09:35.004 --> 01:09:38.298
I really haven't been too good this year.

833
01:09:38.382 --> 01:09:41.217
- Yeah.
- I'm kind of upset about it.

834
01:09:41.302 --> 01:09:43.511
because I really like my family.

835
01:09:43.596 --> 01:09:46.139
Even though sometimes I say I don't.

836
01:09:46.223 --> 01:09:49.642
Sometimes I even think I don't.
Do you get that?

837
01:09:49.727 --> 01:09:54.230
I think so. How you feel about
your family is a complicated thing.

838
01:09:54.315 --> 01:09:57.859
Especially with an older brother.

839
01:09:57.943 --> 01:10:02.197
Deep down you always love 'em.
but you can forget that you love 'em.

840
01:10:02.281 --> 01:10:05.033
And you can hurt them.
and they can hurt you.

841
01:10:05.117 --> 01:10:08.870
And that's not just
because you're young.

842
01:10:08.954 --> 01:10:12.207
You want to know the real reason
that I'm here right now?

843
01:10:12.291 --> 01:10:14.209
Sure.

844
01:10:14.293 --> 01:10:17.921
I came to hear my granddaughter sing.
and I can't come and hear her tonight.

845
01:10:18.005 --> 01:10:23.676
- You have plans?
- No. I'm not welcome.

846
01:10:23.761 --> 01:10:27.597
- At church?
- Oh. you're always welcome at church.

847
01:10:27.681 --> 01:10:30.099
I'm not welcome with my son.

848
01:10:30.184 --> 01:10:34.896
Years back. before you and
your family moved on the block.

849
01:10:34.980 --> 01:10:37.523
I had an argument with my son.

850
01:10:37.608 --> 01:10:41.861
- How old is he?
- Oh. he's grown up.

851
01:10:41.946 --> 01:10:44.572
We lost our tempers.

852
01:10:44.657 --> 01:10:47.659
and I said I didn't care
to see him anymore.

853
01:10:47.743 --> 01:10:52.664
He said the same. and we haven't
spoken to each other since.

854
01:10:52.748 --> 01:10:55.583
If you miss him.
why don't you call him?

855
01:10:55.668 --> 01:10:58.419
I'm afraid if I call him.
he won't talk to me.

856
01:10:58.504 --> 01:11:00.713
How do you know?

857
01:11:00.798 --> 01:11:03.800
I don't know.
I'm just afraid he won't.

858
01:11:03.884 --> 01:11:07.595
No offense. but aren't you
a little old to be afraid?

859
01:11:07.680 --> 01:11:11.266
You can be a little old
for a lot of things.

860
01:11:11.350 --> 01:11:13.601
You're never too old to be afraid.

861
01:11:13.686 --> 01:11:16.437
That's true. I've always
been afraid of our basement.

862
01:11:16.522 --> 01:11:19.983
It's dark. there's weird stuff
down there. and it smells funny.

863
01:11:20.067 --> 01:11:23.486
That sort of thing.
It's bothered me for years.

864
01:11:23.570 --> 01:11:26.030
Basements are like that.

865
01:11:26.115 --> 01:11:29.033
Then I made myself go down there
to do some laundry.

866
01:11:29.118 --> 01:11:31.119
and I found out it's not so bad.

867
01:11:31.203 --> 01:11:33.496
All this time
I've been worrying about it.

868
01:11:33.580 --> 01:11:35.873
but if you turn on the lights.
it's no big deal.

869
01:11:35.958 --> 01:11:40.420
- What's your point?
- My point is you should call your son.

870
01:11:40.504 --> 01:11:42.588
What if he won't talk to me?

871
01:11:42.673 --> 01:11:46.009
At least you'll know. Then you
could stop worrying about it.

872
01:11:46.093 --> 01:11:48.720
and you won't have to be
afraid anymore.

873
01:11:48.804 --> 01:11:52.390
I don't care how mad I was.
I'd talk to my dad.

874
01:11:52.474 --> 01:11:54.392
especially around the holidays.

875
01:11:54.476 --> 01:11:57.645
I don't know.

876
01:11:57.730 --> 01:12:00.898
Just give it a shot.
Foryour granddaughter anyway.

877
01:12:00.983 --> 01:12:04.360
I'm sure she misses you...
and the presents.

878
01:12:04.445 --> 01:12:06.321
I send her a check.

879
01:12:06.405 --> 01:12:10.742
I wish my grandparents send that.
They always send me clothes.

880
01:12:10.826 --> 01:12:13.745
Last year I got a sweater
with a big bird knitted on it.

881
01:12:13.829 --> 01:12:17.123
- Oh. that's nice.
- Not for a guy in the second grade.

882
01:12:17.207 --> 01:12:20.168
You can get beat up
for wearing something like that.

883
01:12:20.252 --> 01:12:22.420
- Oh?
- Yeah.

884
01:12:22.504 --> 01:12:26.632
I have a friend who got nailed 'cause there
was a rumor he wore dinosaur pajamas.

885
01:12:26.717 --> 01:12:30.011
You'd better run along home
where you belong.

886
01:12:30.095 --> 01:12:32.013
You think about what I said.

887
01:12:32.097 --> 01:12:33.890
- All right?
- Okay.

888
01:12:33.974 --> 01:12:37.894
- It was nice talking to you.
- Nice talking to you.

889
01:12:37.978 --> 01:12:40.605
[ Choir ]
♪ Merry. merry Christmas
On. on they send ♪

890
01:12:40.689 --> 01:12:43.691
♪ On without end
Their joyful tone to every home ♪

891
01:12:43.776 --> 01:12:47.111
- What about you?
- Me?

892
01:12:47.196 --> 01:12:49.197
Yeah. You and your son.

893
01:12:49.281 --> 01:12:52.617
We'll see what happens.

894
01:12:52.701 --> 01:12:57.663
Merry Christmas.

895
01:12:57.748 --> 01:12:59.832
♪ One seems to hear words of good cheer ♪

896
01:12:59.917 --> 01:13:02.210
♪ From everywhere Filling the air ♪

897
01:13:02.294 --> 01:13:04.504
♪ Oh. how they pound Raising the sound ♪

898
01:13:04.588 --> 01:13:07.799
♪ O'er hill and dale Telling their tale ♪

899
01:13:50.384 --> 01:13:54.470
This is my house.
I have to defend it.

900
01:15:21.975 --> 01:15:25.937
Okay. we'll check it out first.
We can always come back for the truck.

901
01:15:32.528 --> 01:15:34.779
How do you wanna go in?

902
01:15:34.863 --> 01:15:38.324
We'll go to the back door.
Maybe he'll let us in. You never know.

903
01:15:38.408 --> 01:15:41.911
Yeah. He's a kid.
Kids are stupid.

904
01:15:43.914 --> 01:15:47.833
Bless this nutritious microwavable
macaroni and cheese dinner...

905
01:15:47.918 --> 01:15:49.961
and the people who sold it on sale.

906
01:15:50.045 --> 01:15:51.963
Amen.

907
01:16:15.821 --> 01:16:18.698
This is it.
Don't get scared now.

908
01:16:32.004 --> 01:16:34.463
[ Harry ]
Merry Christmas. little fella.

909
01:16:34.548 --> 01:16:37.133
We know that you're in there.

910
01:16:37.217 --> 01:16:40.136
and that you're all alone.

911
01:16:40.220 --> 01:16:42.888
[ Marv ]
Yeah. come on. kid. Open up.

912
01:16:42.973 --> 01:16:46.517
It's Santy Claus and his elf.

913
01:16:47.894 --> 01:16:50.187
We're not gonna hurt you.

914
01:16:50.272 --> 01:16:54.233
No. no. We got
some nice presents for you.

915
01:16:54.318 --> 01:16:57.778
Be a good little fella now
and open the door.

916
01:17:00.699 --> 01:17:03.451
Shoot!

917
01:17:03.535 --> 01:17:07.330
What? What? What?

918
01:17:07.414 --> 01:17:10.458
What? What happened?

919
01:17:10.542 --> 01:17:14.170
Get that little—

920
01:17:23.472 --> 01:17:25.640
Hello.

921
01:17:30.937 --> 01:17:33.439
Yes! Yes!

922
01:17:33.523 --> 01:17:35.608
The little jerk is armed!

923
01:17:35.692 --> 01:17:39.612
That's it! That's it!
I'm goin' around the front!
You go down the basement!

924
01:17:39.696 --> 01:17:42.156
That little—

925
01:18:18.443 --> 01:18:20.528
Ow!

926
01:18:42.134 --> 01:18:44.385
That smart aleck.

927
01:20:12.057 --> 01:20:17.019
Oh. boy. that's it. you little—
you little son of a—

928
01:20:17.103 --> 01:20:20.105
Oh. not this time. you little brat.

929
01:20:23.693 --> 01:20:26.153
You little creep. you. where are you?

930
01:20:26.238 --> 01:20:30.449
Where are you. you little creep?

931
01:20:50.178 --> 01:20:54.098
Yes! Yes!
